lize the role community leaders play in the current literature and reclaim the everyday lives of Hasidic Jews.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHasidismxHistory. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aAssaf, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAssaf, David.1 aCooper, Levi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Levi.1 aGellman, Uriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGellman, Uriel.1 aHasan-Rokem, Galit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasan-Rokem, Galit.1 aKatz, Maya Balakirsky, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKatz, Maya Balakirsky.1 aLevin, Vladimir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevin, Vladimir.1 aMagid, Shaul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagid, Shaul.1 aPetrovsky-Shtern, Yohanan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetrovsky-Shtern, Yohanan.1 aSagiv, Gadi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSagiv, Gadi.1 aSeroussi, Edwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeroussi, Edwin.1 aWodzinski, Marcin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWodziński, Marcin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065352640uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880425840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978804258423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978804258/original  a978-3-11-065352-6  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBA